This describes the various parameter files (and hence physics
configurations) we are examining



1. brill-lindquist-res256.par and brill-lindquist-res512.par

The original setup

par_b = 0.375       # half separation
par_m_plus = 0.5    # mass of m+ puncture
par_m_minus = 0.8   # mass of m- puncture

R_max = 10.0        # outer boundary
T_max = 10.0        # simulation end time
T_fine = 10.0       # begin of fine output

Another run:
T_max = 4.25        # simulation end time
T_fine = 4.0        # begin of fine output



2. brill-lindquist-2-res256.par

Shortly before common MOTSs form

par_b = 0.5         # half separation
par_m_plus = 0.5    # mass of m+ puncture
par_m_minus = 0.8   # mass of m- puncture

R_max = 9.0         # outer boundary
T_max = 5.5         # simulation end time
T_fine = 5.5        # begin of fine output

Another run:
T_max = 4.75        # simulation end time
T_fine = 3.5        # begin of fine output



3. brill-lindquist-3-res256.par

A little longer before common MOTSs form

par_b = 0.6         # half separation
par_m_plus = 0.5    # mass of m+ puncture
par_m_minus = 0.8   # mass of m- puncture

R_max = 9.5         # outer boundary
T_max = 6.0         # simulation end time
T_fine = 6.0        # begin of fine output

Another run:
T_max = 5.25        # simulation end time
T_fine = 3.25       # begin of fine output



4. brill-lindquist-4-res256.par

Higher mass ratio (1:4) with common MOTSs already formed

par_b = 0.375        # half separation
par_m_plus = 1.0     # mass of m+ puncture
par_m_minus = 0.25   # mass of m- puncture

R_max = 8.5          # outer boundary
T_max = 5.0          # simulation end time
T_fine = 5.0         # begin of fine output

Another run:
T_max = 3.25         # simulation end time
T_fine = 3.0         # begin of fine output

Note: mass ratio is inverted, i.e. m+ > m- ?



5. brill-lindquist-5-res256.par and brill-lindquist-5-res512.par

Largest separation d=1.3

par_b = 0.65        # half separation
par_m_plus = 0.5    # mass of m+ puncture
par_m_minus = 0.8   # mass of m- puncture

R_max = 10.0        # outer boundary
T_max = 5.75        # simulation end time
T_fine = 5.0        # begin of fine output



